column5: Heading up to Uncle Jack's with Crappieperchhunter for the afternoon crappie bite today...Last chance we can because the lake becomes a fish sanctuary after tomorrow (closed Mar 01 to May 18 incl.)  Hope to make a report later this evening...  We are targetting crappie but perch and pickerel are welcome to pull on our strings also
good luck ..hope you have more action then we did on saturday. look fwd to the report
Good Luck Norm, have a Crappie time  Joey

Terry called it...we had fun!!! Beauty day...mild, no wind, lotsa sun...  Both CPH and I hooked sumpin' but  hit the quick release button too soon...several bites but nadda...  A couple of photos is all we got for 4 hours of hard fishing...01:30 to 05:30 pm  Crappieperchhunter   Yours truly   We did see some crappie caught by others nearby so they are still in there if anybody is heading up Wednesday (last chance this season)  A vexilar would have been handy...tough fishing crappie blind.
Norm,you had a good time either way,gorgeous dayand a few missed fish too boot.thats why they call it fishing LOL.  Steve

The weather was great and the company was too. Thanxs Beansie. It was nice to do some hardwater with my summer Carp Point fishing buddy. The C&R we....um..er... practiced....yeah that's right... practiced.... yesterday means more fish the next time we sneak up there.
